2011-07-06T14:37:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/chavez-plans-venezuela-cabinet-changes-today-el-mundo-says.html
Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez  will
announce changes to his Cabinet today, replacing Vice President
Elias Jaua with Foreign Minister Nicolas Maduro and Defense
Minister Carlos Mata Figueroa with General-in-Chief Henry Rangel Silva,  El Mundo  reported, citing unnamed government officials.  Former Ambassador to the Organization of American States
Roy Chaderton will be appointed foreign minister and Chavez is
considering finding a new role within his team for Oil Minister
 Rafael Ramirez , the Caracas-based daily said.  A government official, who isnâ€™t authorized to speak
publicly, said there are no confirmed events with the president
